results.title: And the Best is Yet to Come
Where Little Happy Bluebirds Fly...
results.description: Dazzler contacts the X-Men to help her try and save Longshot from Mojo.

results.title: On the Yard!
results.description: Rogue rescues a mutant Skrull from the Blood Brothers; The X-Men spring Bishop from an alien prison.

results.title: The X-Men vs. The X-Men! (Again) with our special guests...the X-Men!
results.description: The X-Men help Longshot overthrow Mojo to make way for his sequel.

results.title: One Tin Soldier Rides Away...
results.description: Kitty writes a letter to Xavier explaining her resignation from the X-Men as she travels to Russia to spread Peter's ashes; Magneto kills the other Neo and recruits Domina to his cause.

results.title: Prelude to Destruction
results.description: Story is news coverage about Magneto's demand that humanity submit to his rule, or he will be forced to begin a global war from his base in Genosha.

results.title: Eve of Destruction Part 2: A Call to Arms
results.description: Cyclops and Wolvie lead a two man surgical strike on Genosha to clear a way for wounded human refugees to escape to Wakanda.

results.title: Eve of Destruction Conclusion
results.description: It's all out war between the X-Men, old and novice, against Magneto; Wolverine kills Magneto.

X-Statix Vol. 4: X-Statix Vs. the Avengers (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Broken Mirrors
results.description: After his father dies (actually, is killed by Maverick in X-Men #11), Carter Ryking kidnaps his boyhood friend Professor X to try and figure out what their fathers were working on at a genetic research facility when the two were kids.

results.title: Hazardous Territory
results.description: The X-Men try to save Xavier from Hazard.

results.title: Fingers on the Trigger
results.description: Xavier is rapidly dying after being infected by the techno-organic virus; Mr. Sinister trades the captured Scott and Jean for mysterious genetic material; Apocalypse is woken up to deal with the events rocking the mutant world; Cable arrives from the future to find that he is wanted for the shooting of Xavier; The X-Men and X-Factor chase down X-Force before finding out that the hunters have become the hunted.

results.title: The Camel's Back
results.description: The X-Folk mop up the MLF; Stryfe goes to confront Apocalypse.

results.title: Conflicting Catheoes
results.description: It is a battle royale through Stryfe's moon base to try and reach him before he kills Scott and Jean.

results.title: A Skinning of Souls Part One: Waiting for the Ripening
results.description: The X-Men travel to Russia to visit Colossus' parents.

results.title: A Skinning of Souls Part Two: The Crops Mature
results.description: The X-Men battle Omega Red and the Skinner of Souls in Russia.

results.title: A Skinning of Souls Part Three: Harvest of the Innocent
results.description: The Russian government plans on using Illyana to stop the Soul Skinner but kills her parents to get to her; The X-Men stop the Skinner and save Illyana, but not before Colossus experiences even more loss.

results.title: Firestorm
results.description: The Prof and X-Men Blue are captured and taken to Asteroid M; Magneto discoveres that Moira altered his genetic structure when he was a child in her care; The rest of the X-Folk are told they must rescue their team-mates before the Magneto Protocols are implemented.

results.title: Digging in the Dirt
results.description: The X-Men return from Russia and try to get on with their lives after the death of Peter's parents; A second Betsy shows up to confront Psylocke.

results.title: The Puzzle Box
results.description: A team of X-Men travel to Japan to try to unlock the secret of the two Psylockes.

results.title: The Mask Behind the Facade
results.description: The Origin of the two Psylockes is revealed; The Psylocke that has been with the X-Men since Uncanny #256 is an assassin named Kwannon who was imprinted with Betsy Braddock's memories after the latter passed through the siege perilous; Revanche is the original Psylocke; Cyclops runs up against Mr. Sinister in Alaska.

results.title: Leaning Towards Oneself
results.description: Sinister discusses the virus (Legacy) that Stryfe unleashed; Cyclops faces off with the Dark Riders; Kwannon and Betsy Braddock try to sort out their minds; Professor X and Wolverine discuss rumors of Magneto.

results.title: Digging Deeper Between Hope and Sorrow
results.description: Jubilee mourns Ilyana; Rogue and Gambit go on a date; Betsy and Kwannon try to decide who's who.

results.title: Fatal Attractions: The Death of a Dream
Fatal Attractions: Dreams Fade
results.description: The X-Men head up an all out assault on Avalon; Magneto pulls all of the adamantium out of Wolverine's body; Professor X shuts off Magneto's mind; When the X-Men return to earth, Colossus stays behind to care for the fallen foe.

results.title: Bloodties Part 2: Civil Disobedience!
results.description: Going against the U.N.'s orders and fighting their way through SHIELD to do so, the Avengers head to Genosha to rescue Luna from Cortez with the X-Men not far behind.

results.title: A Song of Mourning, A Cry of Joy
results.description: A trio of X-Men come to help Infectia who is dying of the Legacy Virus only to run up against Sinister and a new mutant; Revanche has the Legacy Virus as well.

results.title: Devil in the House
results.description: The X-Men try to adjust to Sabretooth running loose in the Mansion at Xavier's request and Jean decides to teach him a little lesson in manners.

results.title: Return to Hellfire !
results.description: Warren and Betsy attend a party thrown by the Hellfire Club and Shinobi tries to get them to join his ranks.

results.title: Fallout!
results.description: Cortez betrays his master and Asteroid M is destroyed with the X-Men escaping just in time.

results.title: X-Men (1991) #30
results.description: The wedding of Scott Summers and Jean Grey.  After years of fighting alongside each other, Cyclops and the former Marvel Girl tie the knot.

results.title: The Ties That Bind
results.description: Scott and Jean finally get hitched; Xavier reads his farewell letter from Wolverine.

results.title: Soul Possessions Part One: The Butterfly and the Hawk
results.description: Revanche cuts out her Mojo given bionic eyes before leaving the X-Men to finish business with Matsuo as she is dying from the Legacy Virus; Spiral comes after Psylocke.

results.title: Soul Possessions Part Two: The Leopards and the Cats
results.description: Spiral puts the X-Men on the track of unraveling the full mystery of Psylocke and Revanche; Betsy figures it out, puts her demons to rest and begins to move on.

results.title: The Hearts of Thieves
results.description: Sabretooth tries to drive a rift between lovers by telling Rogue of his first encounter with a true rogue named Gambit.

results.title: Life and Consequences
results.description: The X-Men invade Sinister's lab to find out what he knows about the Legacy Virus only to find Threnody running the place.

results.title: X-Men (1991) #36
results.description: PHALANX COVENANT tie-in! The forces of the Phalanx are hunting down the next generation of mutant heroes! Can the X-Men save them before they’re assimilated?

results.title: The Phalanx Covenant Book One Generation Next Part 2: Drop the Leash
results.description: The X-Folk try to save the next generation of mutants from being assimilated by the Phalanx.

results.title: X-Men (1991) #37
results.description: PHALANX COVENANT tie-in! The epic conclusion to the GENERATION NEXT! Witness the final confrontation between Harvest and the mutant heroes.  Who will make the ultimate sacrifice?

results.title: The Phalanx Covenant Book One Generation Next Part 4: The Currents Shift
results.description: The Phalanx makes a final bid for capturing the next generation of new mutants; Blink sacrifices herself to save the team and end the threat.

results.title: Smoke and Mirriors
results.description: Beast continues to investigate the Legacy Virus; Iceman and Rogue go for a dip; Psylocke and Jean train with their psychic powers; Gambit battles Sabretooth in the Danger Room.

results.title: Birds of a Feather
results.description: Scott's grandfather crashes his plane in the mountains of Canada, and Adam X-Treme is the only one around to rescue him.

results.title: The Resurrection and the Flesh
results.description: The Hand brings Omega Red (formerly Arkady) back to life; The X-Men play basketball, mutant style; Moira agonizes over her part in the Magneto fiasco and leaves; Gambit and Rogue are on the way to a chaperoned date when Omega Red and the Hand interfere.

results.title: The Killing Time
results.description: The X-Men try to find their missing teammates who vanished in battle with Legion; Legion and the missing X-Men are twenty years in the past with Magneto and Xavier in Israel; Lilandra warns Xavier that Legion's actions in the past may disrupt all of reality; Meanwhile...back at the mansion, Sabretooth breaks out of his holding cell and is confronted by Wolverine.

results.title: Dreams Die
results.description: In the past, Legion's plan to kill Magneto before he can turn on Xavier comes to fruition; With the killing stroke, Xavier sacrifices himself to save his friend; In the present, the X-Men wait as the world as they know it ends; Thus begins the Age of Apocalypse.

results.title: Heaven Can Wait
results.description: Exodus brings an unknown mutant onto Avalon seeing it as a sign of good fortune; The mutant turns out to be Holocaust from the Age of Apocalypse who starts picking off the Acolytes; Voght turns to the X-Men for help and brings Cyclops and Jean to Avalon where a battle is going on.

results.title: Falling From Grace
results.description: The battle between Exodus and Holocaust tears Avalon apart; Scott, Jean and the Acolytes try to shield themselves from a fiery re-entry.
